==Alexander Bogdanov==

Orsan Senalp:

"Primary insight I reached, from the research I am doing on Alexander Bogdanov's life work (to be refined): In a comparable way and in sequence with the overarching scientific revolutions of the axial age and the Rennaissance / Reformation period (as the main leaps in the developmental path of human scientific thought and knowledge in general), Bogdanov's work indicate a contemporary major revolution, which is ongoing. Bogdanov's work is so far the single one, which could scientifically overcome the subject-object dualism, the core contradiction the modern science (which looked at the subject scientifically for the first time and thought of it as seperate from the object world). Without Bogdanov's paradigm, or with its loss, the subject-object dualism made its apex with the 'wrong' post-modernism of the 1980s and 90s. When subject and absolute relativity was defended against or attacked at any holistic and integral scientific approach aiming to find a solution to this dualism. In the absence of an answer to subject-object dualism problem, structuralism, systems and cybernetics paradigms couldn't stand well before the post-structuralist and post-modern offensive."

(https://www.facebook.com/groups/322508360006/?multi_permalinks=10163751060795007)

